  1. Press Release: Annapolis Acting City Attorney Linda Schuett Announces Departure

    Annapolis Acting City Attorney Linda Schuett announced her resignation to Mayor Gavin Buckley and the Office of Law staff on Tuesday, April 16, 2019. Schuett has been the acting City Attorney for six weeks. Read on...

  2. Press Release: Annapolis City Closures for Spring Holidays and Observances

    In observance of religious holidays including Good Friday, Easter, and Passover, the City of Annapolis will have the following schedule changes... Read on...

  3. Press Release: “Diaspora: A Black Heritage Celebration” Moving Indoors to Stanton Center

    The “Diaspora: A Black Heritage Celebration,” scheduled for April 13th from 2 to 6 p.m. has been moved from to the Stanton Center, 92 W. Washington St. This African American cultural entertainment event will commence after the 2019 MLK Jr. parade. Read on...

  1. 2020 Comprehensive Plan
